<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<ecoSpold xmlns="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02 ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02.xsd http://www.EcoInvent.org/UsedUserMasterData ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02UserMasterData.xsd">
  <childActivityDataset>
    <activityDescription>
      <activity specialActivityType="0" id="9222940a-158b-5a18-a0f2-e81d74f17280" activityNameId="d9dd728b-bbc8-476f-9ae5-32d0fe25be74" parentActivityId="eeca4507-3b37-55ef-925a-8e66dafacfec" inheritanceDepth="-1" type="1">
        <activityName xml:lang="en">ozone production, liquid</activityName>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">Ozon</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">Ozone heavy work</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">Ozone light work</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">10028-15-6</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">Triatomic oxygen</synonym>
        <includedActivitiesStart xml:lang="en">The activity starts when the raw materials enter the process.</includedActivitiesStart>
        <includedActivitiesEnd xml:lang="en">This activity ends with the production of liquid ozone. The dataset includes the energy consumption, and an estimation of the cooling water and infrastructure. Not included is the input of 38.2 kg air (representing 8 kg of oxygen) and the output of the remaining parts of this input (such as nitrogen, carbon dioxide, oxygen, etc.).</includedActivitiesEnd>
        <generalComment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This dataset represents the production of 1 kg of liquid ozone. Ozone is an irritating and pale blue gas, very toxic and explosive. It is a very strong and powerful oxidizing agent and is always produced on a demand basis at its point of use. Ozone is primarily used for the treatment of drinking water and wastewater.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">This dataset is based on a rough estimation of the consumption of main raw materials and energy, and should therefore be used only for processes where the impact of ozone is not considered to be high. The consumption of cooling water is based on data from a large chemical factory (Gendorf 2016).</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="2">References:</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="3">Hischier R. (2007) Life Cycle Inventories of Packagings &amp; Graphical Papers. ecoinvent report No. 11, Swiss Centre for Life Cycle Inventories, Dübendorf, 2007.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="4">Kirschner, M. J. 2000. Ozone. Ullmann's Encyclopedia of Industrial Chemistry.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="5">Gendorf (2016) Umwelterklärung 2015, Werk Gendorf Industriepark, www.gendorf.de.</text>
        </generalComment>
      </activity>
      <classification classificationId="28f738cc-bb73-48f8-b633-f83fb9bc5ddc">
        <classificationSystem xml:lang="en">ISIC rev.4 ecoinvent</classificationSystem>
        <classificationValue xml:lang="en">2011:Manufacture of basic chemicals</classificationValue>
      </classification>
      <geography geographyId="7846b897-7c04-4f9f-b607-2b83fcd9a74c">
        <shortname xml:lang="en">RoW</shortname>
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">Data used for energy are from the EU-IPPC report and represent the average European situation. The data are assumed to be representative of the global production.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">References:</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="2">European Commission (2001) Integrated Pollution Prevention and Control (IPPC) - Reference Document on Best Available Techniques in the Pulp and Paper Industry. Institute for Prospective Technological Studies, Sevilla. Some values are based on data from a large chemical factory located in Germany. These are assumed to be valid for this geography.</text>
        </comment>
      </geography>
      <technology technologyLevel="3">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">Production of ozone from air in a corona discharge system. </text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">References:</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="2">Hischier R. (2007) Life Cycle Inventories of Packagings &amp; Graphical Papers. ecoinvent report No. 11, Swiss Centre for Life Cycle Inventories, Dübendorf, 2007.</text>
        </comment>
      </technology>
      <timePeriod startDate="2000-01-01" endDate="2023-12-31" isDataValidForEntirePeriod="true">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">The data in this dataset come from different years, but overall form the most realistic picture of the production. Some values are based on data published by the Gendorf factory that were collected between 2011 and 2015. The time period has been adjusted accordingly. For more details, see the comments of the exchanges.</text>
        </comment>
      </timePeriod>
      <macroEconomicScenario macroEconomicScenarioId="d9f57f0a-a01f-42eb-a57b-8f18d6635801">
        <name xml:lang="en">Business-as-Usual</name>
      </macroEconomicScenario>
    </activityDescription>
